## Memory Management Guidelines

### Creating Errors

```c
// Errors are created with sc_error_create() - always returns heap-allocated memory
sc_unified_error_t *err = sc_error_create(SC_DOMAIN_PALETTE, 1001, 404,
                                           "Palette '%s' not found", id);
```

### Handling Errors

```c
// At the point where the error is handled (not propagated), destroy it
sc_unified_error_t *err = some_function_call();
if (err != NULL) {
    // Log or use the error
    log_error("Error: %s", err->message);

    // Build response
    build_http_response(err->http_status_code, err->message);

    // MUST destroy when done
    sc_error_destroy(err);
    return;
}
```

### Propagating Errors

```c
// When propagating errors up the call stack, pass ownership without destroying
sc_unified_error_t *err = lower_layer_call();
if (err != NULL) {
    // Just return the error - caller is responsible for cleanup
    return err;
}
```

